autosave.description: Configure used for automatically saving configurations.

interval-time.description: The system automatically saves configurations every a specified interval.

delay-time.description: When the system configuration changes, the system automatically saves the configuration after a specified delay.

cpu-limit.description: Upper limit of the CPU usage for automatically saving configurations.

lock-username.description: Name of a user who locks the configuration.

lock-time.description: Time when the configuration is locked.

identifier.description: Unique ID of a configuration lock.

unlock-username.description: Name of a user who unlocks the configuration.

unlock-time.description: Time when the configuration is unlocked.

checkpoints.description: List of all configuration checkpoints in the system.

checkpoint.description: Operational state of configuration checkpoints in the system.

user-label.description: Label for identifying a configuration checkpoint, which is a character string that does not start with a digit.

username.description: Name of the user who committed a configuration to trigger the generation of a configuration checkpoint.

line.description: Instance of the terminal accessed by the user who committed a configuration to trigger the generation of a configuration checkpoint.

client.description: Type of the tool agent accessed by the user who committed a configuration to trigger the generation of a configuration checkpoint.

timestamp.description: Time when a configuration checkpoint was created.

description.description: Description of a configuration checkpoint. A user can set a description for a configuration checkpoint to be generated when committing a configuration.

current-point-changes.description: List of configuration change information recorded in all configuration checkpoints. List of the configuration change information recorded in each configuration checkpoint is separately displayed.

current-point-change.description: Operational state of configuration change between a specified configuration checkpoint and the previous configuration checkpoint.

index.description: Index of a configuration change. A configuration checkpoint records a configuration change after a configuration is committed. Each configuration change is identified by an index.

since-point-changes.description: List of configuration changes between a specified configuration checkpoint and the current configuration.

since-point-change.description: Operational state of configuration change between a specified configuration checkpoint and the current configuration.

index.description: Index of a configuration change. A configuration checkpoint records a configuration change after a configuration is committed. Each configuration change is identified by an index.

global-switch.description: Configure the globally configuration management feature.

configuration-slave-detect-switch.description: Enable/disable function to automatically verify the configurations of the master and slave main control boards.

appdata-detect-switch.description: Enable/disable function to automatically verify application data.

checkpoint-switch.description: Enable/disable switch of saving check ponit.

backup-and-recovery-states.description: List of operation states delivered by the NMS.

backup-and-recovery-state.description: Operational state of a configuration file.

index.description: Operation ID.

operation-type.description: Operation type delivered by the NMS.

autosave-checkpoint.description: Configure start-time for automatically saving checkpoint.

start-time.description: The system automatically save checkpoint at a specified time of the day.

configuration-operation-cpu-limit.description: Configure the CPU supress on configuration operation.

snmp-cpu-limit.description: CPU usage threshold that triggers rate limiting on users that access through SNMP.

snmp-switch.description: Enable/disable function of CPU usage-based rate limiting for users that access through SNMP.

netconf-cpu-limit.description: CPU usage threshold that triggers rate limiting on users that access through NETCONF.

netconf-switch.description: Enable/disable function of CPU usage-based rate limiting for users that access through NETCONF.

backup-servers.description: List of backup servers. A maximum of five backup servers can be configured.

backup-server.description: Configure backup server used for automatically saving uploaded files.

server-ip.description: IP address of the backup server.

transport-type.description: Type of the protocol for transporting the backup file.

username.description: User name for connecting the backup server.

password.description: Password for connecting the backup server.

path.description: Path for backing up the configuration file.

startup-infos.description: List of information about system startup.

startup-info.description: Operational state of information about a system startup.

configed-system-software.description: File name of the system software that is set by users for the current startup.

current-system-software.description: File name of the system software that is applied for the current startup.

next-system-software.description: File name of the system software that is applied for the next startup.

current-cfg-file.description: Name of the configuration file that is applied for the current startup.

next-cfg-file.description: Name of the configuration file that is applied for the next startup.

current-patch-file.description: Name of the patch file that is applied for the current startup.

next-patch-file.description: Name of the patch file that is applied for the next startup.

cfg-file.description: Operational state of the specified configuration file that a user can set for the next startup or the information about the difference to current configuration.

create-time.description: Time when a configuration file was created, for example, 2010-11-04 20:01:38 +08:00.

file-current-changes.description: List of differences between a specified configuration file and the current configuration.

file-current-change.description: Operational state of a specified configuration file different with the current configuration.

index.description: Index of the configuration difference. Each configuration difference has an index.

config-rollback-result.description: Operational state of rollbacking configuration result.

config-recover-results.description: List of all configuration restoration results in the system.

config-recover-result.description: Operational state of configuration restoration result in the system.

index.description: Index of a configuration command. Each failure command is identified by an index.

command.description: Configure the command that fails to be restored.

view.description: View of a command that fails to be restored.

line.description: Row number of a command that fails to be restored in a file.

reason.description: Cause of the configuration restoration failure command.

time.description: The command failed to be executed during configuration restoration.

configuration-backup-to-file.description: Configure the start-time and interval for cycle backup the current configuration operation.

interval-time.description: The system automatically backups configurations every a specified interval day.

start-time.description: The system automatically backups running configuration at a specified time of the day.

config-change.description: Operational state of SN of a configuration change. The SN increases by 1 for each configuration change.

flow-id.description: SN of the current configuration change of the system.

baseline-time.description: Time when the system configuration has a major change, for example, 2012-07-19 14:57:44 +08:00.
